-- Egypt Planning to Build $700 Million Solar Power Plant, Al Ahram Reports
-- Ola Galal
-- 2010-07-10T12:44:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-10/egypt-plans-to-build-700-million-solar-power-plant-al-ahram-reports.html

          
          
             Egypt plans to build a 4 billion
Egyptian-pound ($700 million) solar power plant in the south of
the country, Al Ahram newspaper reported today, citing
Electricity Minister Hassan Younes.  
 The plant, which will be located at Kom Ombo in Aswan
province, will be financed by institutions including the African
Development Fund, according to the Cairo-based newspaper.  
